The paper discusses reinforcement learning agents that learn to solve sequential decision tasks by interacting with the environment. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses the incorporation of human guidance, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The tasks being solved may involve robotics (cs.RO) or computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.HC, cs.RO, and cs.CV.
